CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 23, 1953, pg. 16, reads: "Politicking - Former Republican Chairman of the Fifth Ward, David Thompkins, is shown discussing the complex election situation last Tuesday at Wadsworth Hall (Eighteenth District, Fifth Ward). Reading from left to right are Donald Myers, Sallie Reaves, Mary Ellen Pennywell, Thompkins, and Catherine Butler. Thompkins supported the winning Malone - Kane - Whitten ticket. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Donald Myers, Sallie Reaves, Mary Ellen Pennywell, Republican Chairman of Fifth Ward David Thompkins holding "Dressler for County Clerk" broadside, and Catherine Butler standing in front of Wadsworth Hall with campaign signs, Hill District
